pullRequest.body:
---
I'm going to use Continued Fraction for denumerability of Q. We don't need continued fractions to prove the cardinality of Q and we don't need cardinals to prove denumerability of Q. So I seperated the files, and made a new file for the lemma about the cardinality of Q.

I also golfed the proof of denumerability, it's slightly shorter if I use the proof of encodability.

The proof of `Cardinal.mkRat` is just `Cardinal.mk_eq_aleph0`, however the set of imports required to make this proof work is not obvious, so I think it's still worth keeping the lemma.

I wasn't sure what to do with the copyright header in the new file. I just copied the one from the `denumerable` file and added Floris Van Doorn as an author as he wrote the cardinality lemma.
